file.name: Analytics_Insights.txt
file.title: Analytics Insights
file.preview:
Inbox /Message Usage: Put this in the wishlist Google doc:
§  From the data, since the beginning of 2017, about 16.34% of returning member visits touched message or inbox pages. About 34.26% of returning members touched either pages. Most of the messages still happened on DT, about 41%. From the data, as the threads get longer, the % of messages which happened on DT decreased rather than increased. (This makes sense to me since I think they tend to reply back on any device available rather than just desktop.)
o    Triggers Answers: I think this is the best you will have to work with. Analytics didn’t give me any more than I could find, but I am pushing:
§  Seeker – we know most if they post a job (vs. enroll). If they posted a job:
·         1. what they are looking for

<!channel> I think we experienced a bit of a breakthrough in Stand Up today (at least I did). Here's my reflection of it. Please REVIEW and let me know if you agree or if you're of a different understanding:

1. Jason to map Ivan’s feature audit atop 
- Identify gaps as well as areas of adequate coverage
2.  Based on <@U4VTSDW7P> and <@U0XJFPSRL> analysis of message threads and CRM data, map paintpoints or emotional moments on top of features and user journey
- Analyze for opportunities
3. Apply <@U0XCJ372R> analysis of industry do’s and don’ts to identify OPPORTUNITIES

These OPPORTUNITIES need to be understood end-to-end as a NARRATIVE arc. This NARRATIVE arc should include moments where OPPORTUNITIES can be exploited.  

*This is the thinking we will take to client on Wednesday. As words and as diagrams/UX thinking.*
